Task 1 - basic task 
 
 1. ~$ ls     #it listed all of the files in my current directory 
 2. ~$ pwd    #it shows the current directory where I am working 
 3. ~$ mkdir Workspace
    ~$ cd Workspace 
 4. ~$ ls     #when ls is typed nothing execute. I am working on a file that is in my directory where currently no files have been added.
 5. ~/Workspace$ touch README.md
 6. ~/Workspace$ cp README.md ./CHANGELOG.md
 
 
 Task 2 - Absolute and Relative Paths
 
 ~/Workspace$ touch exercise.md
 ~/Workspace$ mv exercise.md /tmp/
 ~/Workspace$ cd /tmp
 /tmp$ ls
 /tmp$ rm exercise.md
 /tmp$ ls
 
 Task 3 - Cat Commands 
 
 //home/recruit$ cd Workspace 
 
 1/2. 
 //home/recruit/Workspace$ cat > umuzi.md
 umuzi is in jeppestown, johannesburg and is a non-governmental organisation
 //home/recruit/Workspace$ cat > recruits.md
 umuzi recruits are cool and awesome 
 //home/recruit/Workspace$ cat > cohort.md
 i belong to  cohort 20 Data Eng 
 
 3. //home/recruit/Workspace$ cat umuzi.md recruits.md cohort.md
 
 4/5.
   //home/recruit/Workspace$ cat umuzi.md recruits.md cohort.md -> summary.md
   The End 
   //home/recruit/Workspace$ cat summary.md
   
   
 Task 4 - The Locate Command 
   
 1. //home/recruit/Workspace$ locate umuzi 
 2. //home/recruit/Workspace$ cd ~
      ~$ touch search_results.md
      ~$ ls
      ~$ locate umuzi
      ~$ locate umuzi > search_results.md
      ~$ cat search_results.md
      
 
 Task 5 
 1. ~$ cd ~/Documents
    ~/Documents$ touch pad.md
 2. ~/Documents$ cd ~/Desktop
    ~/Desktop$ mkdir Work
 3. ~/Desktop$ cd ~/Documents
    ~/Documents$ cp pad.md ./pad_copy.md
    ~/Documents$ ls 
 4. ~/Documents$ locate updatedb
 5. ~/Documents$ cd ~/Desktop
 6. ~/Desktop$ locate pad_copy.md
 
 
 Task 6 - Find Commands 
 1. ~$ find ~/ -name *.pdf
 2. ~$ find ~/ -name *.pdf > searchresults
    ~$ ls
    ~$ cat searchresults
    ~$ cp searchresults ~/Desktop
    
 3. ~$ find . type f -newermt 2020-01-16 -ls
 
       
